  "name": "Bacillus subtilis 168",
  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 120,
    "description": "Curated contaminant-anchor roster \u00d7 CDS GCF_000009045.1 ASM904v1 (NCBI, public domain). 14 loci: the TCA growth backbone citZ + the sporulation cascade (spo0A master regulator, sigF/sigE/sigG, spoIIE, spoVG, the cotE coat morphogen, the sspA/sspB DNA-armour SASPs) + the gerAA germination receptor + oxidative-defence katA/sodA. B. subtilis 168: 4,214,810 bp / ~4,100-4,300 genes; the endospore (CaDPA ~25 % core dry wt, multilayer coat) survives heat/desiccation/UV/radiation for years-millennia -> defeats the sterilization barrier (97 % of NASA cleanroom isolates were spore-formers). The immigration kernel reads role + trait levers, not specific genes (ADR-019 S0).",
    "temp_optimum": 0.55,
    "parent_key": null,
    "trophic_role": "decomposer"
  },
